\begin_layout Section
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Transcranial electric and magnetic stimulation is a set of techniques used
 to modulate the cortical neuronal activity utilizing the external source
 of electric or magnetic field applied on the scalp.
 The field non-invasively affects cortical tissue to few centimeters beneath
 the skull, therefore it interferes with cortical gyri and to a limited
 extent with cortical sulci as well.
 The field causes depolarisation or hyperpolarisation of the neuronal membranes
 in affected tissue which is accompanied by changes in neuronal excitability
 or in case of higher intensities also by formation of action potentials
 in neurons.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This techniques have therapeutic and diagnostic applications in psychiatry,
 neurology, neurophysiology, etc.
 
\end_layout

